By GARBA MUHAMMAD, Kaduna Scores of students were kidnapped from an Islamic School, Sunday, in Tegina, Rafi Local Government of Niger State. Though unconfirmed reports put the number of kidnapped students at about 200, Mary Noel Barje, Chief Press Secretary to Niger State Governor, while confirming the kidnap, however said the number of the abducted students was not yet ascertained. “Yes there was an abduction at an Islamic School in Tegina. “But we are yet to ascertain the number of student abducted. “Search and rescue is ongoing,” she said Sunday evening. MINNA - Students and staff members of the Government Science College Kagara, Niger State, who were kidnapped by bandits, were yet to be released Sunday night.A highly-placed security source had told The PUNCH that the abductees were on their way to Minna from around the Birnin Gwari area of Kaduna… In "Top Stories" Renowned Islamic Scholar, Sheikh Abubakar Gumi, on Friday, met with the Governor of Niger State, Abubakar Bello, over the abduction of students and members of staff of Government Science College, Kagara. Photos of Gumi meeting with some bandits in a forest in Niger State surfaced online on Friday. The Islamic… In "News" Gunmen on Friday (early this morning) abducted yet to be ascertained number of schoolgirls from Government Girls Secondary School, Jangebe in Talata Mafara local government area of Zamfara state. However, in a developing story on BBC Hausa, about 300 felames students were said to have been abducted. This is coming… In "Top Stories"